A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Linda J. Davidson upon her retirement; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Linda J. Davidson joined the Alzheimer's Association as the executive director
4 of the Georgia Chapter in June 2017, and she has since demonstrated exceptional leadership
5 in donor management and team development as well as served as a driving force behind the
6 organization's growth; and
7 WHEREAS, the Alzheimer's Association is the leading voluntary health organization in
8 Alzheimer's care, support, and research as well as the voice for Alzheimer's disease
9 advocacy, fighting for critical care initiatives at the state and federal level; and
10 WHEREAS, Linda's expertise has proven invaluable in growing the reach and services of
11 the Alzheimer's Association for the more than 150,000 Georgia residents living with
12 Alzheimer's and other forms of dementia; and
13 WHEREAS, prior to her position with the Alzheimer's Association, Linda diligently worked
14 with United Way and Catholic Social Services as well as served as the senior director of
15 Relay For Life for the American Cancer Association; and
